block.flf rusty-figlet v0.1.0 placeholder
[PLACEHOLDER] rusty-figlet v0.1.0 Phase 1 scaffolded placeholder font.

This font is a syntactically-valid FIGfont 2.0 placeholder generated during
T022 in specs/00009-figlet-port/tasks.md. It satisfies the parser's required
glyph coverage (ASCII 32..=126 plus the 7 German chars 196/214/220/228/246/
252/223) so the FR-013 parser tests pass and the bundled-font include_bytes!
table compiles. Polish-phase work MUST replace these placeholders with the
verbatim cmatsuoka figlet 2.2.5 upstream font files; see THIRD_PARTY.md.

Each glyph is a single line wide enough to satisfy `max_length`; for ASCII
32..=126 the literal codepoint character appears followed by hardblank ($)
padding. For the 7 German chars the cell uses a 2-letter ASCII mnemonic so
the file remains pure ASCII. Renderings are NOT visually representative of
the upstream font this file is named after.
